		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Please Lose Battle</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi everyone,<br /><br />I can't tell whether it' s the right place or not to talk to you about what follows, but here it is : retro gaming and music are my two passions and I own a home recording studio in France. <br /><br />I got the chance to work with a band called <a href="http://www.please-lose-battle.com/" class="postlink">Please Lose Battle</a> from France too.<br />It's a multiform chiptune band : there is a bass, drums, NES for melodies and live video is projected with very cool pixel art patterns and characters moving along with the music. It's super powerful, super coloured and live definitely reaches a new dimension thanks to this.<br /><br />So we recorded their last album together and it was released with the help of <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Cheapbeats/?fref=ts" class="postlink">Cheapbeats</a>, a chiptune label based it Tokyo, Japan. You can listen to it <a href="https://pleaselosebattle.bandcamp.com/album/goodbye-joy" class="postlink">here</a>.<br /><br />I know for sure that some of you have enough curiosity to have a look so here are the links to the <a href="https://vimeo.com/153247620" class="postlink">studio teaser/report</a> and to their <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCzdv_zo-uPINJCITgUeCjmw" class="postlink">youtube</a> page where you'll find a live footage and a clip !<br /><br />Enjoy and feel free to share/comment if it turns out you like it... or not !

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


